### addVariantDeclaration() {#aaf2fe2b910650ab4ea0eeaca5922dce8}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static void addVariantDeclaration (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/callinst">CallInst</a> &amp; CI, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/elementcount">ElementCount</a> &amp; VF, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/vecdesc">VecDesc</a> &#42; VD)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
A helper function that adds the vector variant declaration for vectorizing the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/callinst">CallInst</a> <code>CI</code> with a vectorization factor of <code>VF</code> lanes.

For each mapping, TLI provides a VABI prefix, which contains all information required to create vector function declaration.

Definition at line <a href="#l00040">40</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/transforms/lib/transforms/utils/injecttlimappings-cpp">InjectTLIMappings.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>
